#: ../../../release-notes.rst:202
msgid ""
"v0.4.1 is primarily a polishing release, focusing on bug fixes, UX "
"improvements, and security-related fixes (with four low-to-moderate severity "
"GHSA reports published). However, a substantial amount of effort has also "
"been invested in improving the Venom pipeline, resulting in better "
"performance and code generation from the Venom pipeline. Venom can be "
"enabled by passing the ``--venom`` or ``--experimental-codegen`` flag to the "
"Vyper compiler (they are aliases of each other). Venom code can now also be "
"compiled directly, using the ``venom`` binary (included in this release)."
msgstr ""

