#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1348
msgid ""
"This is a major breaking release of the Vyper compiler and language. It is "
"also the first release following our versioning scheme (`#1887 <https://"
"github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1887>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1352
msgid ""
"``@public`` and ``@private`` function decorators have been renamed to "
"``@external`` and ``@internal`` (VIP `#2065 <https://github.com/vyperlang/"
"vyper/issues/2065>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1353
msgid ""
"The ``@constant`` decorator has been renamed to ``@view`` (VIP `#2040 "
"<https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/2040>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1354
msgid ""
"Type units have been removed (VIP `#1881 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/"
"issues/1881>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1355
msgid ""
"Event declaration syntax now resembles that of struct declarations (VIP "
"`#1864 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1864>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1356
msgid ""
"``log`` is now a statement (VIP `#1864 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/"
"issues/1864>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1357
msgid ""
"Mapping declaration syntax changed to ``HashMap[key_type, value_type]`` (VIP "
"`#1969 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1969>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1358
msgid ""
"Interfaces are now declared via the ``interface`` keyword instead of "
"``contract`` (VIP `#1825 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1825>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1359
msgid ""
"``bytes`` and ``string`` types are now written as ``Bytes`` and ``String`` "
"(`#2080 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/pull/2080>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1360
msgid ""
"``bytes`` and ``string`` literals must now be bytes or regular strings, "
"respectively. They are no longer interchangeable. (VIP `#1876 <https://"
"github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1876>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1361
msgid ""
"``assert_modifiable`` has been removed, you can now directly perform "
"assertions on calls (`#2050 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/pull/2050>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1362
msgid ""
"``value`` is no longer an allowable variable name in a function input (VIP "
"`#1877 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1877>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1363
msgid ""
"The ``slice`` builtin function expects ``uint256`` for the ``start`` and "
"``length`` args (VIP `#1986 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/"
"issues/1986>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1364
msgid ""
"``len`` return type is now ``uint256`` (VIP `#1979 <https://github.com/"
"vyperlang/vyper/issues/1979>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1365
msgid ""
"``value`` and ``gas`` kwargs for external function calls must be given as "
"``uint256`` (VIP `#1878 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1878>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1366
msgid ""
"The ``outsize`` kwarg in ``raw_call`` has been renamed to ``max_outsize`` "
"(`#1977 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/pull/1977>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1367
msgid ""
"The ``type`` kwarg in ``extract32`` has been renamed to ``output_type`` "
"(`#2036 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/pull/2036>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1368
msgid ""
"Public array getters now use ``uint256`` for their input argument(s) (VIP "
"`#1983 <https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/1983>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release-notes.rst:1369
